.TH "sigmadsp_setup" 9 "sigmadsp_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sigmadsp_setup \- Setup the DSP for the specified samplerate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sigmadsp_setup
.BI "(struct sigmadsp *sigmadsp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int samplerate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sigmadsp" 12
The sigmadsp instance to configure
.IP "samplerate" 12
The samplerate the DSP should be configured for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Loads the appropriate firmware program and parameter memory (if not already
loaded) and enables the controls for the specified samplerate. Any control
parameter changes that have been made previously will be restored.

Returns 0 on success, a negative error code otherwise.
